where PME, s is the main engine’s output power at the simulated service speed (Vs); SFCs is the specific fuel consumption at the selected power load measured in t/kWh, and D is the sailing distance between the departure and arrival ports estimated in nautical miles. In this way, the yearly fuel saving amount resulted from speed reduction measure (∆Ftotal) estimated in t/year can be evaluated as displayed in Eq. (2) depending on the expected number of round trips per year (NT) and the amount of fuel saving (Elkafas and Shouman 2021).2ΔFNT,s=∑NT=1NTFC0-FCs\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
